05/03/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Council of Europe (CoE) Secretary General Walter Schwimmer said Thursday (4 March) that Europe highly values Albania's role in regional stability and integrity. 
During his official visit to Albania, Schwimmer presented the new CoE representative to the country. 
While in Tirana, he also met with President Alfred Moisiu, Prime Minister Fatos Nano and Parliament Speaker Servet Pellumbi. 
As for recent political turmoil, Schwimmer suggested strengthened political dialogue in order to meet the country's main objectives -- fighting corruption and implementing reforms. 
(ATA - 04/03/04)
